# Android Manifest Standards

## Required Permissions Checklist

Every permission must be present. Verify before any release:

```xml
<!-- Network -->
<uses-permission android:name="android.permission.INTERNET" />
<uses-permission android:name="android.permission.ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE" />

<!-- Location (staggered: FINE + COARSE at onboarding, BACKGROUND only when convoy created) -->
<uses-permission android:name="android.permission.ACCESS_COARSE_LOCATION" />
<uses-permission android:name="android.permission.ACCESS_FINE_LOCATION" />
<uses-permission android:name="android.permission.ACCESS_BACKGROUND_LOCATION" />

<!-- Foreground service types (Android 14+ requires explicit types) -->
<uses-permission android:name="android.permission.FOREGROUND_SERVICE" />
<uses-permission android:name="android.permission.FOREGROUND_SERVICE_LOCATION" />

<!-- Bluetooth for P2P mesh and SCO audio -->
<uses-permission android:name="android.permission.BLUETOOTH_ADVERTISE" />
<uses-permission android:name="android.permission.BLUETOOTH_CONNECT" />
<uses-permission android:name="android.permission.BLUETOOTH_SCAN" />
<uses-permission android:name="android.permission.NEARBY_WIFI_DEVICES" />

<!-- IMU crash detection + Activity Recognition -->
<uses-permission android:name="android.permission.ACTIVITY_RECOGNITION" />

<!-- SCO audio routing to Cardo/Sena helmet -->
<uses-permission android:name="android.permission.MODIFY_AUDIO_SETTINGS" />
<uses-permission android:name="android.permission.BLUETOOTH" />

<!-- Signal recovery beacon -->
<uses-permission android:name="android.permission.READ_PHONE_STATE" />

<!-- SOS notifications -->
<uses-permission android:name="android.permission.POST_NOTIFICATIONS" />

<!-- Battery optimization bypass prompt -->
<uses-permission android:name="android.permission.REQUEST_IGNORE_BATTERY_OPTIMIZATIONS" />
```

## Foreground Service Declaration

```xml
<service
    android:name=".service.ConvoyForegroundService"
    android:foregroundServiceType="location"
    android:exported="false" />

<service
    android:name=".service.GarageSyncWorker"
    android:exported="false" />
```

`foregroundServiceType="location"` is mandatory for Android 14+ background location access.

## Staggered Permission Rationale

Do NOT request all permissions at launch. Request just-in-time:

| Permission | When to Request |
|-----------|-----------------|
| `ACCESS_FINE_LOCATION` | On first map open |
| `ACCESS_BACKGROUND_LOCATION` | When convoy session is created |
| `BLUETOOTH_*` / `NEARBY_WIFI_DEVICES` | When "Join Convoy" is tapped |
| `ACTIVITY_RECOGNITION` | On first launch (needed for crash detection) |
| `MODIFY_AUDIO_SETTINGS` | When helmet integration is configured |
| `READ_PHONE_STATE` | When dead-zone signal recovery is explained |
| `POST_NOTIFICATIONS` | Before starting any background service |

Each request must show a rationale screen explaining the safety purpose (required for Play Store background location approval).

## Google Play Background Location Declaration

Background location requires a video demonstrating:
1. The rider mounting their phone
2. The app running in the background
3. The convoy link remaining active while screen is off
4. The SOS detection working without foreground

Keep this video at `docs/play-store/background-location-justification.mp4`.

## Minimum SDK

```xml
<uses-sdk
    android:minSdkVersion="26"
    android:targetSdkVersion="35" />
```

Min SDK 26 (Android 8.0) required for: Nearby Connections API stability, BLE advertising, foreground service types.
